<paragraph id="8BA936DBC10AFFEFFF32F8C6C7AFF8D8" blockId="18.[151,1196,1829,1851]" box="[151,1196,1829,1851]" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">
<taxonomicName id="4C164D58C10AFFEFFF32F8C6C130F8D8" authority="Fabricius, in Bryk, 1938" authorityName="Fabricius, in Bryk" authorityYear="1938" box="[151,563,1829,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Castnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marius">
<emphasis id="B962EAC9C10AFFEFFF32F8C6C231F8D8" box="[151,306,1830,1851]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">Castnia marius</emphasis>
Fabricius, in Bryk, 1938
</taxonomicName>
: 
<emphasis id="B962EAC9C10AFFEFFD99F8C6C77DF8D8" box="[572,1150,1829,1851]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">J. Chr. Fabricius Systema Glossatorum (Brunovici 1807)</emphasis>
: 67.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30C6550C10AFFEEFF32F887C238FEA3" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="264" pageId="18" pageNumber="263" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BA936DBC10AFFEFFF32F887C053F80F" blockId="18.[151,1437,1895,2029]" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis id="B962EAC9C10AFFEFFF32F887C24AF863" bold="true" box="[151,329,1895,1920]" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">Type material.</emphasis>
Fabricius stated “Dom. Smidt Mus. D. Lund.”. It was thought possible that the holotype (by monotypy) may be in ZMC but after searching the Fabricius and Sehested/Tönder-Lund collections, as well as the 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D58C10AFFEFFF32F850C20EF82A" authorityName=", Moraes &amp; Duarte" authorityYear="2014" box="[151,269,1968,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Castniidae</taxonomicName>
in the general collection of the museum, this and other 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D58C10AFFEFFC34F850C71EF82B" box="[913,1053,1968,1992]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Haemonides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="263" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B962EAC9C10AFFEFFC34F850C71EF82B" box="[913,1053,1968,1992]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="263">Haemonides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens were not found so we must assume that the type is lost (Ole Karsholt, pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA936DBC10BFFEEFF62FF77C076FF1B" blockId="19.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis id="B962EAC9C10BFFEEFF62FF77C266FF53" bold="true" box="[199,357,151,176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">
<typeStatus id="54AD8879C10BFFEEFF62FF77C201FF53" box="[199,258,151,176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Type</typeStatus>
locality.
</emphasis>
&quot;America meridionali&quot; (South America). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B2AC10BFFEEFC9CFF78C70CFF53" author="Brown" box="[825,1039,152,176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" refString="Brown, F. M. (1988) Fabricius's &quot; Systema Glossatorum. &quot; Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 113 (4), 431 - 446." type="journal article" year="1988">Brown (1988: 438)</bibRefCitation>
hypothesised that the 
<typeStatus id="54AD8879C10BFFEEFAADFF77C669FF53" box="[1288,1386,151,176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected in St. Croix, 
<collectingCountry id="F301764BC10BFFEEFE06FF5CC147FF36" box="[419,580,188,213]" name="Virgin Islands" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
by Smidt. However, it is possible that it came from 
<collectingCountry id="F301764BC10BFFEEFB1CFF5CC613FF37" box="[1209,1296,188,212]" name="Guyana" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Guyana</collectingCountry>
instead (cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B2AC10BFFEEFF32FF00C24AFF1B" author="Papavero" box="[151,329,224,248]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" refString="Papavero, N. (1971) Essays on the history of Neotropical Dipterology, with special reference to collectors (1750 - 1905). Vol. I. Universidade de Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia, Sao Paulo, [8] + vii + 216 pp." type="book chapter" year="1971">Papavero, 1971</bibRefCitation>
: 21–22). The locality cannot be further restricted.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA936DBC10BFFEEFF62FEE4C238FEA3" blockId="19.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis id="B962EAC9C10BFFEEFF62FEE4C2A2FEFE" bold="true" box="[199,417,260,285]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Taxonomic status.</emphasis>
A junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D58C10BFFEEFC86FEE5C09DFEFF" box="[803,926,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Haemonides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cronida">
<emphasis id="B962EAC9C10BFFEEFC86FEE5C09DFEFF" box="[803,926,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">H. cronida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Herrich-Schäffer [1854]). Synonymised by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B2AC10BFFEEFF32FEC8C234FEA3" author="Lamas" box="[151,311,295,320]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" refString="Lamas, G. (1995) A critical review of J. Y. Miller's checklist of the Neotropical Castniidae (Lepidoptera). Revista peruana de Entomologia, 37, 73 - 87." type="journal article" year="1995">Lamas (1995)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30C6550C10BFFEEFF62FEACC1D0FE86" box="[199,723,332,357]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BA936DBC10BFFEEFF62FEACC1D0FE86" blockId="19.[151,1436,151,501]" box="[199,723,332,357]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis id="B962EAC9C10BFFEEFF62FEACC263FE86" bold="true" box="[199,352,332,357]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Distribution.</emphasis>
Not relevant, see 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D58C10BFFEEFD8EFEACC182FE87" box="[555,641,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Haemonides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cronida">
<emphasis id="B962EAC9C10BFFEEFD8EFEACC182FE87" box="[555,641,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">cronida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
above.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30C6550C10BFFEEFF62FE8FC631FE17" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA936DBC10BFFEEFF62FE8FC631FE17" blockId="19.[151,1436,151,501]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">
<emphasis id="B962EAC9C10BFFEEFF62FE8FC24FFE6B" bold="true" box="[199,332,367,392]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">Discussion.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D58C10BFFEEFE77FE90C123FE64" authorityName="Fabricius, in Bryk" authorityYear="1938" box="[466,544,368,391]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Castnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marius">
<emphasis id="B962EAC9C10BFFEEFE77FE90C123FE64" box="[466,544,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">marius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only became available after 1938 when Felix Bryk (
<date id="FFA8101BC10BFFEEFB23FE8FC604FE6B" box="[1158,1287,367,392]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" value="1882" valueMax="1957">1882–1957</date>
) published a facsimilar edition of the (incomplete) “Systema Glossatorum” of Fabricius, hence the rather strange date to be associated with 
<bibRefCitation id="EF874B2AC10BFFEEFEF0FE57C18CFE33" box="[341,655,439,464]" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1938) Systema glossatorum secundum ordines, genera, species adiectis synonymis locis, observationibus, descriptionibus. In: Bryk, F. (Ed.), J. Chr. Fabricius Systema Glossatorum (Brunovici 1807). G. Feller, Neubrandenburg, pp. [i] - xii, 13 - 112." type="journal article">Fabricius. Fabricius (1938)</bibRefCitation>
also listed Cramer’s 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D58C10BFFEEFC37FE58C0D4FE2C" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[914,983,440,463]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cronis">
<emphasis id="B962EAC9C10BFFEEFC37FE58C0D4FE2C" box="[914,983,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">cronis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the same work. Had the “Systema Glossatorum” been published during Fabricius’s lifetime, 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D58C10BFFEEFC85FE3DC06DFE17" authorityName="Fabricius, in Bryk" authorityYear="1938" box="[800,878,477,500]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Castnia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marius">
<emphasis id="B962EAC9C10BFFEEFC85FE3DC06DFE17" box="[800,878,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">marius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would have taken priority over 
<taxonomicName id="4C164D58C10BFFEEFB70FE3CC628FE17" box="[1237,1323,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Haemonides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="264" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cronida">
<emphasis id="B962EAC9C10BFFEEFB70FE3CC628FE17" box="[1237,1323,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="264">cronida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
